  "title": "Network Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Epergne Solutions is looking for a Network Engineer We are looking for a skilled with strong expertise in campus networking, network security, and enterprise access control solutions. The role involves designing, implementing, securing, and supporting wired and wireless networks, firewall technologies, and zero-trust security platforms in a large enterprise environment.<br /></p><h3>Required Skills & Qualifications</h3><ul><li><p>Strong experience in <strong>campus wired and wireless networking</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on expertise with <strong>Infoblox DDI</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience managing <strong>firewalls</strong> and <strong>Zscaler ZIA/ZPA/ZTNA</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Practical knowledge of <strong>Cisco Catalyst Center</strong> and <strong>Cisco ISE</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of networking protocols (TCP/IP, VLANs, routing, switching).</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of security best practices and zero-trust principles.</p></li><li><p>Excellent troubleshooting and documentation skills.</p></li></ul><h3>Preferred Qualifications</h3><ul><li><p>Cisco certifications (CCNP, CCIE – Enterprise or Security).</p></li><li><p>Experience in large enterprise or global network environments.</p></li><li><p>Exposure to cloud networking and hybrid architectures.</p></li><li><p>ITIL or similar operational experience.</p></li></ul><p><strong></strong></p><p> </p>",
